  en: "Yes, Kearse and Ligaj successfully demonstrated that Epicoccum nigrum can produce red pigmentation on wheat wafers that superficially resembles blood. However, this result only concerns red fungal growth, not cardiac tissue, not blood, and certainly not intact white blood cells infiltrating the myocardium.",
